Articles.Content: So just installed a number of mods and notised like alot of my parts are no longer in the game. like not even in the Science tree in fact some portions are completely blank

If one of the mods is old and the .cfg files are not up to date, it can cause an exception that will keep all parts from loading. You are going to have to remove all mods, then add them back in one at a time to pinpoint the offending mod. Is this a major pain? yeah, kinda, I don't think there is going to be an easier way though. Maybe post a list of mods you are using to see if anyone can spot or recognize potential problems.

There are a few possibilities. More information, particularly your output log, would help narrow down the problem. If you're not sure where that is, read the [thread=92229]How to Get Support[/thread] sticky.
